description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an Epilepsy Clinical Nurse Specialist to join the Paediatric Neurology Team at the Noah’s Ark Childrens Hospital for Wales. The successful candidate will work alongside other members of the Multi-disciplinary Team- the Paediatric Neurology Consultant and Specialist Ketogenic Dietician in order to establish a Paediatric Ketogenic Diet Service in South Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are searching for someone who shares our values that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We care about the people we serve and the people we work with&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We trust one another&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We respect each other&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We take personal responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We treat people with kindness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We act with integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate should demonstrate significant post registration experience within the Paediatric Neurology field and be a dynamic, motivated and forward thinking individual who possesses the drive and ambition to help shape our services to enable us to make a real difference to the lives of children with epilepsy and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Claire Thirsk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: CNS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: claire.thirsk@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 02921841945&lt;/p&gt;
